Uses of Package
sharepointapp

  • Classes in sharepointapp used by sharepointapp 
    Class and Description
    SharePointAuthenticator
    This class is used for authenticating users for a SharePoint server/site.
    SharePointMainController
    This is the class responsible for communicating between the different views and for managing different processes.
    SharePointMainController.GetItemsThread
    This class is used to populate the item view in a new thread, allowing the GUI not to be frozen during the process.
    SharePointWebController
    This class is used to connect to a SharePoint site and for reading its data.
    SharePointWebController.Connector
    This class is responsible for loading the site.
    SPBaseView
    This class is used to represent the base for the views used in this project.
    SPFolder
    This class is used to represent a collection of items.
    SPItem
    This class represents an item/file/folder received from SharePoint.
    SPItem.ItemType
    This enum represents the different things an item can represent.
    SPItemView
    This class is used to show all of the items associated with a particular list/library.
    SPListView
    This class is used to present the lists associated with a SharePoint site.
    SPPreferences
    This class allows values to be stored during current and future runs of the program.
    SPPreferencesWindow
    This class creates a view that allows a user to see all of the saved preferences and to edit them.
    SPPreferencesWindow.PrefElement
    This class represents the information from one preference key, displaying all of the values in a table.
    SPToolbarView
    This class is responsible for showing the toolbar buttons, messages, and url input.
